1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,320
Hello, English learners.
你好，英语学习者。

2
00:00:04,320 --> 00:00:05,760
Welcome back to EnglishPod.
欢迎回到EnglishPod。

3
00:00:05,760 --> 00:00:06,760
My name is Marco.
我叫Marco。

4
00:00:06,760 --> 00:00:08,000
And my name is Catherine.
我叫Catherine。

5
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,000
And today, I think we're hitting the gym, Marco.
今天，我想我们要去健身房了，Marco。

6
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,400
We need to be healthy.
我们需要保持健康。

7
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,280
We've gained weight over the winter, I think.
我想我们冬天长胖了。

8
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:15,280
I think so.
我也这么觉得。

9
00:00:15,280 --> 00:00:19,560
And being in an office, you know, it doesn't give you much opportunity to go and exercise
而且待在办公室里，你知道，没什么机会去运动，

10
00:00:19,560 --> 00:00:22,520
and really get a lot of work done during the day.
白天真的很难完成很多锻炼。

11
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:23,520
Exactly.
没错。

12
00:00:23,520 --> 00:00:25,520
So that's why we're going to the gym on this occasion.
所以这就是为什么这次我们要去健身房。

13
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:27,400
We're going to be pumping some iron.
我们要举铁了。

14
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:28,800
We're going to be working out.
我们要锻炼了。

15
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:33,800
So why don't we take a look at Vocabulary Preview and see what this means.
那我们来看看词汇预览，了解一下这是什么意思。

16
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:34,800
Vocabulary Preview.
词汇预览。

17
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:35,800
All right.
好的。

18
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:37,640
So, to pump iron, what does that mean?
那么，“pump iron”是什么意思？

19
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:38,640
All right.
好的。

20
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:41,080
Well, to pumping iron means lifting weights.
嗯，“pump iron”就是举重。

21
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:42,080
Okay.
好的。

22
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:43,280
So we're pumping iron.
所以我们在举铁。

23
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:44,280
We're lifting weights.
我们在举重。

24
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:45,960
Because, you know, weights are made of iron.
因为，你知道，杠铃是铁做的。

25
00:00:45,960 --> 00:00:46,960
Right.
对。

26
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:47,960
That's what makes them so heavy.
这就是它们这么重的原因。

27
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:48,960
All right.
好的。

28
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:49,960
So we're pumping iron.
所以我们在举铁。

29
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:50,960
Good.
好。

30
00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:53,200
And, well, we're going to be giving you guys some pointers.
而且，我们会给你们一些建议。

31
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,200
Pointers.
建议。

32
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:55,200
Right.
对。

33
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:56,200
All right.
好的。

34
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:57,200
So you might have heard the word point before.
你可能以前听过“point”这个词。

35
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,920
And pointers is another word for tips.
“Pointers”是“tips”的另一种说法。

36
00:00:58,920 --> 00:00:59,920
All right.
好的。

37
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:01,440
So we're going to be giving you tips or advice.
所以我们会给你们一些提示或建议。

38
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:02,440
Yeah.
是的。

39
00:01:02,440 --> 00:01:04,240
So you're going to get some help today from the trainer.
所以今天你会从教练那里得到一些帮助。

40
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:05,240
All right.
好的。

41
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:06,840
So we're going to jump right into this dialogue.
那我们直接进入对话吧。

42
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:16,280
And when we come back, we'll be talking more about what's going on.
等我们回来，我们会再聊聊发生了什么。

43
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:17,280
Hey there.
嘿，你好。

44
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:18,280
You look a little lost.
你看起来有点迷茫。

45
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:19,280
Are you new here?
你是新来的吗？

46
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,280
Yeah.
是的。

47
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:22,200
How did you know?
你怎么知道的？

48
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:23,960
You can always spot the newbies.
你总能认出新手。

49
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:25,800
I can give you a few pointers if you want.
如果你愿意，我可以给你一些建议。

50
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:27,800
Were you trying to use this machine here?
你刚才想用这台机器吗？

51
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:28,800
Yeah.
是的。

52
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:32,680
I just started my training today, and I'm not sure where to begin.
我今天刚开始训练，不知道从哪里开始。

53
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,680
It's okay.
没关系。

54
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:35,120
I know how it is.
我懂这种感觉。

55
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:39,800
This machine here will work out your upper body, mainly your triceps and biceps.
这台机器可以锻炼你的上半身，主要是肱三头肌和肱二头肌。

56
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:43,000
Are you looking to develop strength or muscle tone and definition?
你是想增强力量，还是想练肌肉线条和清晰度？

57
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:45,960
Well, I don't want to be ripped like you.
嗯，我不想练得像你那样肌肉发达。

58
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:48,920
I just want a good physique with weights and cardio.
我只想通过举重和有氧运动练出好身材。

59
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:51,400
In that case, you want to work with less weight.
那样的话，你应该用轻一点的重量。

60
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:55,160
You can start off by working 10 to 15 reps in four sets.
你可以从每组10到15次，做四组开始。

61
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,080
Five kilo weights should be enough.
五公斤的重量应该够了。

62
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:59,360
Now it's very important that you stretch before pumping iron.
现在，举铁前拉伸非常重要。

63
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:01,120
You might pull a muscle.
你可能会拉伤肌肉。

64
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,120
Got it.
明白了。

65
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:03,120
Wow.
哇。

66
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,120
Is that the weight you're lifting?
那是你举的重量吗？

67
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:06,800
My goodness, that's a lot of weight.
天哪，那可真重。

68
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:07,960
It's not that much.
没那么重。

69
00:02:07,960 --> 00:02:10,960
Just watch.
看着吧。

70
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:16,360
I'm okay.
我没事。

71
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:22,880
So this guy was a little bit arrogant.
所以这家伙有点自大。

72
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:28,640
I think he was very muscular, but I think he embarrassed himself in front of the lady.
我觉得他肌肉很发达，但他在那位女士面前出丑了。

73
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:29,640
The trainer, you mean?
你是说教练？

74
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:30,640
Yeah.
是的。

75
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:31,640
Yeah, definitely.
对，绝对是。

76
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:33,040
So we say he had a big ego.
所以我们说他自尊心很强。

77
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:35,280
He thought a lot about himself.
他太自以为是了。

78
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:39,360
So let's check out some of these phrases and words that they were using because they're
那我们来看看他们用的一些短语和单词，因为

79
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:42,960
all related to going to the gym, and they can help you if you ever want to get some
这些都和去健身房有关，如果你在健身房需要帮助，

80
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:51,000
help when you're at the gym.
它们能派上用场。

81
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,640
So this girl, she was new in the gym.
所以这个女孩是健身房的新手。

82
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:54,400
She didn't really know what she was doing.
她不太清楚自己在做什么。

83
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:58,840
And well, the guy said, well, do you want to develop strength or muscle tone?
然后那个男的说，你想增强力量还是练肌肉线条？

84
00:02:58,840 --> 00:02:59,840
All right.
好的。

85
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:02,160
We know what strength is, but what is muscle tone?
我们知道力量是什么，但肌肉线条是什么？

86
00:03:02,160 --> 00:03:03,160
Okay.
好的。

87
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:09,360
So if you want to develop muscle tone or to have muscle tone, it means that you have healthy
如果你想练肌肉线条或有肌肉线条，意思是你的肌肉很健康，

88
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:11,640
muscles, not like huge, big muscles, right?
不是那种巨大、夸张的肌肉，对吧？

89
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:13,920
But you have a nice body.
而是身材很好。

90
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:14,920
Right.
对。

91
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:19,640
So tone, to tone is to maybe give some shape to something.
所以“tone”，塑形，就是给某物一些形状。

92
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:24,080
Sometimes you have big arms and you can't see the muscles.
有时候你手臂很粗，但看不到肌肉。

93
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:27,880
Well, muscle tone means that you can start to see the shape and they start to get stronger.
嗯，肌肉线条意味着你能开始看到形状，肌肉也开始变强壮。

94
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:28,880
All right.
好的。

95
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:32,680
So if you think of Madonna, maybe five years ago, she had a lot of muscle tone.
所以如果你想到麦当娜，大概五年前，她肌肉线条很好。

96
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:35,560
Now she's like big muscles.
现在她肌肉很大块了。

97
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:38,720
But muscle tone means that you can see the muscles, they start to develop.
但肌肉线条意味着你能看到肌肉，它们开始发展。

98
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:39,720
Okay.
好的。

99
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:44,880
And this actually is very related to our next word because you said muscle tone and definition.
这其实和我们下一个词很相关，因为你提到了肌肉线条和清晰度。

100
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:45,880
Right.
对。

101
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:50,400
So definition is another way for us to describe seeing those muscles because at first you
所以“definition”是另一种描述看到肌肉的方式，因为一开始

102
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:55,200
have a big tummy or you have big arms and when you start to work out, every time you
你肚子大或手臂粗，当你开始锻炼，每次去，

103
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,620
go, you can see more and more definition.
你会看到越来越清晰的线条。

104
00:03:57,620 --> 00:04:00,080
That means more and more of the muscle becomes visible.
这意味着越来越多的肌肉变得可见。

105
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,080
All right.
好的。

106
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,560
So you have defined muscles.
所以你有清晰的肌肉。

107
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,560
All right.
好的。

108
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:04,560
Good.
好。

109
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,960
Now the girl was like, no, no, I don't want to be like super strong and huge.
现在那个女孩说，不，不，我不想变得超级强壮和巨大。

110
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:09,080
She doesn't want to look like Arnold Schwarzenegger.
她不想看起来像阿诺德·施瓦辛格。

111
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,080
Yeah, exactly.
是的，没错。

112
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,720
She said, I just want a good physique.
她说，我只想要好身材。

113
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:12,720
All right.
好的。

114
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:17,120
So this word maybe sounds strange for some of you because it's more like French than
这个词对你们有些人来说可能听起来有点奇怪，因为它更像法语

115
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,120
English.
而不是英语。

116
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,120
Yeah.
是的。

117
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:22,000
Well, it does come from French and physique is a way to talk about the whole body.
嗯，它确实来自法语，“physique”是描述整个身体的一种方式。

118
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:26,140
You know, the physique is the state of your whole body.
你知道，身材就是你整个身体的状态。

119
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:27,140
It's your physical appearance.
就是你的外貌。

120
00:04:27,140 --> 00:04:28,140
Okay.
好的。

121
00:04:28,140 --> 00:04:30,840
So I can say she has a nice physique.
所以我可以说她身材很好。

122
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:35,200
So that means she's probably works out a lot.
那意味着她可能经常锻炼。

123
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:38,000
So but basically it's like her whole body, right?
但基本上就是她的整个身体，对吧？

124
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:42,200
You can't just say like she has good physique in her arms or something like that.
你不能只说她的手臂身材好之类的。

125
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:45,080
And now your physique, physical, think of the word physical.
现在你的“physique”，身体的，想想“physical”这个词。

126
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:47,080
It's your whole body, your whole body.
是你的整个身体，整个身体。

127
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:48,080
All right.
好的。

128
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,320
So good physique.
所以好身材。

129
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:54,120
And now the tips that he was giving her or the pointers, he was talking about these two
现在他给她的建议或提示，他提到了这两个词：

130
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:56,480
words reps and sets.
“reps”和“sets”。

131
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,480
Right.
对。

132
00:04:57,480 --> 00:05:01,760
These are great words for the gym because they, they allow us to count when we're working
这些是健身房里的好词，因为它们让我们在锻炼时

133
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:02,760
out.
能计数。

134
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:05,040
So the first one is reps or repetitions.
第一个是“reps”或“repetitions”。

135
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:08,840
That means doing something over and over again.
意思是反复做某事。

136
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:16,560
So for example, if I want to lift a weight, I sit down on the bench, I do one, two, three.
比如，如果我想举重，我坐在长凳上，做一、二、三。

137
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:20,280
How many times I lift that weight is a repetition or a rep.
我举多少次就是一次重复或一次“rep”。

138
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:21,280
All right.
好的。

139
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:23,840
And well, and what about sets?
那“sets”呢？

140
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:29,640
So I could say I lift the weight 10 times, one, two, three, four, all the way to 10.
所以我可以说我举重10次，一、二、三、四，一直到10。

141
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:31,960
And then I wait and then I do it again.
然后我休息，然后再做一次。

142
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:35,200
So the number of times I do it again is a set.
所以再做一次的次数就是一组。

143
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:37,720
So sets of 10 or sets of five.
所以是10次一组或5次一组。

144
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:38,720
Okay.
好的。

145
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:45,000
So if you are lifting this weight 10 times and you have five sets, you will do a total
所以如果你举重10次，做五组，你总共会做

146
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:49,520
of 50 pushes or lifts or repetitions.
50次推举或举重或重复。

147
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,520
Okay.
好的。

148
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:55,880
So reps and sets are probably the most important or common words you'll hear in the gym, especially
所以“reps”和“sets”可能是你在健身房听到的最重要或最常见的词，尤其是

149
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:57,040
if you're lifting weights.
如果你举重的话。

150
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,040
Right.
对。

151
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,040
Definitely.
绝对是。

152
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:02,520
And sometimes your trainer will count with you so that he'll, he'll keep a count while
有时候你的教练会和你一起数，这样他会在你锻炼时

153
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:03,880
you're working out.
保持计数。

154
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:04,880
Cool.
酷。

155
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:08,120
So those are the words that we have for you on Language Takeaway.
这些就是我们在语言要点部分为你准备的单词。

156
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:13,320
I think in order to better understand these words, we should listen to our dialogue again,
我觉得为了更好地理解这些词，我们应该再听一遍对话，

157
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:20,280
but we're going to slow it down just a little bit.
但我们会稍微放慢速度。

158
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:21,480
Hey there.
嘿，你好。

159
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:23,060
You look a little lost.
你看起来有点迷茫。

160
00:06:23,060 --> 00:06:24,060
Are you new here?
你是新来的吗？

161
00:06:24,060 --> 00:06:25,060
Yeah.
是的。

162
00:06:25,060 --> 00:06:27,060
How did you know?
你怎么知道的？

163
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:29,200
You can always spot the newbies.
你总能认出新手。

164
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:32,320
I can give you a few pointers if you want.
如果你愿意，我可以给你一些建议。

165
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:34,600
Were you trying to use this machine here?
你刚才想用这台机器吗？

166
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,600
Yeah.
是的。

167
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,400
I just started my training today.
我今天刚开始训练。

168
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:39,840
I'm not really sure where to begin.
我不太确定从哪里开始。

169
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:40,840
It's okay.
没关系。

170
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:42,740
I know how it is.
我懂这种感觉。

171
00:06:42,740 --> 00:06:48,000
This machine here will work out your upper body, mainly your triceps and biceps.
这台机器可以锻炼你的上半身，主要是肱三头肌和肱二头肌。

172
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:51,920
Are you looking to develop strength or muscle tone and definition?
你是想增强力量，还是想练肌肉线条和清晰度？

173
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:55,320
Well, I don't want to be ripped like you.
嗯，我不想练得像你那样肌肉发达。

174
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:59,060
I just want a good physique with weights and cardio.
我只想通过举重和有氧运动练出好身材。

175
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:02,260
